==See also==
[[Image:Rolleiflex camera.jpg|thumb|upright|Later model of the [[Rolleiflex]] camera such as was used by Vishniac in Eastern Europe]]

===Organizations===
* [[International Center of Photography]] &mdash; Owner of the copyrights of Roman's works.
* [[American Jewish Joint Distribution Committee]] &mdash; Originally commissioned Vishniac's trips to Eastern Europe.

===Photography===
* [[Time-lapse]] &mdash; Technique pioneered by Vishniac.
* [[Documentary photography]]

===People===
* [[Wolf V. Vishniac]] &mdash; Son of Roman, eminent [[microbiology|microbiologist]], died in 1973 during an [[Antarctica|Antarctic]] expedition.
* [[Ethan Vishniac|Ethan T. Vishniac]] &mdash; Grandson of Roman, son of Wolf, editor of the [[Astrophysical Journal]].
* [[Cornell Capa]] &mdash; Founder of ICP.
* [[Alter Kacyzne]] &mdash; A well-known contemporary of Roman Vishniac's; photographed similar subjects, but died in a [[concentration camp]] in 1941.
